records.nl_statement: If $C_{0}+\frac{C_{1}}{2}+\cdots+\frac{C_{n-1}}{n}+\frac{C_{n}}{n+1}=0,$ where $C_{0}, \ldots, C_{n}$ are real constants, prove that the equation $C_{0}+C_{1} x+\cdots+C_{n-1} x^{n-1}+C_{n} x^{n}=0$ has at least one real root between 0 and 1.

theorem exercise_5_4 {n : ℕ}

  ∃ x, x ∈ (Set.Icc (0 : ℝ) 1) ∧ ∑ i in range (n + 1), (C i) * (x^i) = 0 :=
